In the first week of an Introduction to Information Technology course, the following activities typically occur:
1. Introduction of the Lecturer and Course: The lecturer introduces themselves and explains the syllabus and course objectives.
2. Overview of Course Material: The lecturer provides an outline of the topics to be covered, including required textbooks and references.
3. Student Introductions: The lecturer may call on students one by one to introduce themselves, often in the order of the attendance list.
4. Explanation of Schedule and Evaluation: The lecturer explains the course schedule, assignments, exams, and grading criteria.
5. Discussion and Q&A: Students have the opportunity to ask questions about the course content or any related matters.
